17/06/2010
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- The foreign ministry confirmed on Wednesday (June 16th) that authorities in Skopje and Pristina are discussing a future investigation into possible mass graves in Macedonia.
Kosovo Ambassador to Macedonia Skender Durmishi says consultations are under way.
Investigators would work to determine if civilians killed by Serbian forces during the 1998-1999 war were buried in Macedonia.
(Zeri, Koha Ditore, Telegrafi, Express, Tanjug - 17/06/10)
